SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 431
By Seal
A RESOLUTION to honor Wayne Rich on being named the 2025
Tennessee 4-H Salute to Excellence
Outstanding Lifetime Volunteer.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly take great pleasure in recognizing
those public-spirited citizens who help the youth of Tennessee develop into responsible citizens
with bright futures; and
WHEREAS, Wayne Rich of Jefferson County has been named the 2025 Tennessee 4-H
Salute to Excellence Outstanding Lifetime Volunteer in appreciation of his dedicated service to
the Jefferson County 4-H Patriot shooting sports team for the last twenty years; and
WHEREAS, he has excelled at teaching youth, fundraising, and advocating for this 4-H
program with leaders and parents in Jefferson County; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Rich founded the team in 2005, and it has since grown to average forty-
five participating youths per year; and
WHEREAS, under his deft leadership, the Jefferson County 4-H Patriot shooting sports
team has earned recognition as the flagship program in Tennessee, having won numerous
trophies and awards on both the State and national levels; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Rich loves to work with young people, and he can teach any youth of
any age the necessary skills to achieve their goals in shooting sports; and
WHEREAS, he also helps recruit and train new volunteers for the program and serves
as a great resource for the adults involved with 4-H; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Rich organizes and coordinates a quail hunt and a bear hunt each year
to provide access to a hunting experience that would otherwise be unavailable for young
people; and
