WHEREAS, involvement in 4-H comes naturally to Mr. Rich; as a youth, he was a 4-H
member in Pickett County, attended 4-H camp at the Clyde M. York 4-H Center in Crossville
each summer, and later served as a member of the camp's staff for six years; and
WHEREAS, Wayne Rich has made a tremendous positive impact on the youth of
Jefferson County through his leadership and commitment to others, and he is worthy of our
approbation as he celebrates this special occasion; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate Wayne Rich on being
named the 2025 Tennessee 4-H Salute to Excellence Outstanding Lifetime Volunteer, applaud
his ongoing commitment to 4-H and the youth of his community, and extend to him our best
wishes for much continued success and happiness.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
